paragraph.content:
to enable a plug having pins, or other forms of contact, of different
                        dimensions or configuration from those of the socket, to be engaged with the
                        socket;

subsection.def:
certificate
                    (證明書) means a document certifying the test
                results of an electrical product;

fuse
                    (熔斷器) has the same meaning as in IEC
                291;

fuse-link
                    (熔斷連桿) has the same meaning as in IEC
                291;

IECEE
                    (國際電工委員會電工產品安全認證組織) means the IEC System for
                Conformity Testing to Standards for Safety of Electrical Equipment;

luminaire
                    (照明器) has the same meaning as in IEC 598
                    Part 1;

supplier
                    (供應商) means a person who supplies an
                electrical product;

thermostat
                    (恆溫器) has the same meaning as in IEC 335
                    Part 1;

tool
                    (工具) has the same meaning as in IEC 335
                    Part 1;

paragraph.content:
persons and animals are adequately protected against danger of physical
                    injury or other harm which might be caused by electrical contact whether direct
                    or indirect;

persons, animals and property are adequately protected against
                    non-electrical danger caused by the electrical product which are revealed by
                    experience;

the electrical product meets the expected mechanical requirements in such a
                    way that persons, animals and property are adequately protected against danger
                    caused by the electrical product;

in foreseeable conditions of overload, persons, animals and property are
                    adequately protected against danger caused by the electrical product;
                    and

a plug forming part of a ceiling rose connector (that is to
                                    say, a connector designed to hold up overhead electric lighting
                                    fittings);

tr.td:
a
                            5A plug and a 3-core flexible cord;
                            and

paragraph.content:
shall be fixed durably and conspicuously on the surface of the packaging of
                    the electrical product, or on the product itself if no packaging is provided
                    when supplied;
